@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@smartwrap
MBMan is a little program that can give you some informations about the
commands in the C: directory. MBMan works exactly the same way as Man 1.21 by
MAUI and MBMan uses the same Manual.txt as Man but MBMan is much faster. This
is achieved by loading the whole Manual.txt into memory instead of reading it
line by line. As a result of that you need some more memory to run MBMan.

MBMan was written in Oberon-A İ1995 by Frank Copeland.

If you use MBMan regularly or you have any comments, bugreports or you want to
pay me for MBMan, even though you don't have to, then feel free to write to me
(see address at the bottom of this document).
@endnode

