@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@smartwrap
MBMan requires OS2.1 or higher.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@smartwrap
Just copy the MBMan program to your C: drawer or somewhere else in your path
and the Manual.txt to your S: drawer. If you want to have localized texts in
MBMan then copy the catalog file for your language to LOCALE:Catalogs/<your
language>/ (At the moment only a Danish and a Swedish catalog is supplied)
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@smartwrap
MBMan can only be started from the Shell.

MBMan supports one argument:

COMMAND      The command you want to know more about.


Press CTRL C to quit MBMan when running.
@endnode

@node "The Manual.txt" "The Manual.txt"
@smartwrap
The Manual.txt has to be located in your S: directory else MBMan will fail.
(The supplied Manual.txt is the same as the one found in MAUI's Man_mw.lha
archive even though I am aware of some errors in this document.)

The format of Manual.txt is (Taken from MAUI's doc. I hope he does not mind):


\@Command

Explanation

Explanation

Explanation

and so on



\@Next Command

Explanation

Explanation

Explanation

and so on

\@

@endnode

@node "Other Stuff By Me" "Other Stuff By Me"
@smartwrap
@{b}AddIcon@{ub}   A program that uses datatypes.library for adding standard icons to
files. Can be found on Aminet in util/wb


@{b}MBClock@{ub}   A simple clock. Can be found on Aminet in util/time


@{b}OberonAModules@{ub}   Some modules for Oberon-A. Can be found on Aminet in
dev/obero


@{b}SortIcons@{ub}   A program that makes it very easy to sort Workbench icons in
alphabetical order. Can be found on Aminet in util/wb


@{b}MoneyManager@{ub}   A nice and free accounting program. Can be found on Aminet in
biz/misc


@{b}SmartView@{ub}   A little utility usefull for everybody who has the Aminet CD's.
can be found on Aminet in util/misc
@endnode

@node "History" "History"
@smartwrap
@{b}02/01/1998 1.00@{ub}

First version.



@{b}26/02/1999 1.01@{ub}

Updated the manual.txt to include LZX 1.21r and LHA 1.94.

Added Swedish and Italian catalog and bumped version of MBMan to 1.01.

Also added German documentation (in plain text) and a German catalog file.

Changed the documentation into an AmigaGuide document.

(No changes to the executable)
@endnode

